  "prompt": "How do you politely turn down someone who wants to \"grab coffee sometime\"?",
  "response": "When turning down an invitation to grab coffee, you can do so politely and respectfully. Here are a few approaches you might consider:\n\n1. **Express Gratitude**: Start by thanking them for the invitation.\n   - \u201cThanks so much for the invite! I appreciate it.\u201d\n\n2. **Be Honest, but Kind**: You can mention your current commitments or preferences without going into too much detail.\n   - \u201cI\u2019m really busy right now and can\u2019t take on any more social outings, but I appreciate the offer!\u201d\n\n3. **Offer an Alternative (if appropriate)**: You might suggest connecting in another way or at a later time.\n   - \u201cI can\u2019t make it for coffee, but let\u2019s stay in touch through email or LinkedIn!\u201d\n\n4. **Direct but Polite**: If you prefer to be straightforward, you can decline gently.\n   - \u201cI\u2019m not able to meet for coffee, but thank you for thinking of me!\u201d\n\nChoose the approach that feels most comfortable for you, and remember that it\u2019s perfectly okay to decline an invitation.",
